      "name": "Basmil Mixed Section",
      "settings": {
        "toc_heading": "Table Of Contents",
        "navigation_label": "Navigate through the chapters:",
        "navigation_btn_text": "Learn More →",
        "color_scheme": "scheme-4",
        "custom_liquid": "<highlight>\nHimalayan cliff honey is an explicitly sourced natural honey from the high-altitude region in the Himalayas of Nepal. Found thousands of metres above sea level- where only limited bee species can survive- the honey is prepared by the extraordinary Himalayan giant honeybee species <em><b>“Apis laboriosa”</b></em>, also known as Himalayan Giant honeybees. Harvested only twice a year, its collection is done following a traditional honey hunting practice, where the native hunters climb towering cliffs risking their lives.\n</highlight>\n<p>\nThe primary floral source of Himalayan cliff honey is rhododendron- the flower has a naturally occurring compound, grayanotoxin, and upon consumption of the honey, consumers can experience a range of symptoms from euphoria to discomfort if consumed in excess. The effects thus experienced have made the honey popular by the name “mad honey”.</p>\n<img src=\"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0686/0721/3628/files/Frame_1984079214_1c33a902-6b4f-4588-8986-c6a306413038.webp?v=1768969037\" alt=\"rhodonderon\" width=\"980\" height=\"980\" style=\"max-width:100%; width:100%; height:auto;\">\n\n<p>\nNow, with this brief and easy-to-understand overview of Himalayan cliff honey, there are still much more mysteries left to be uncovered. This guide is intended to serve you with all of it, the comprehensive information on this unparalleled gift from the Himalayas; moreover, a deeper insight into how this panacea has been valued through time awaits to be explored!\n</p>\n<style>\n{% assign sid = '#shopify-section-' | append: section.id %}\n\n{{ sid }} .icons-grid {\ndisplay:flex;\nflex-wrap:wrap;\n--gap:clamp(8px,1.67vw,32px);\ngap:var(--gap)!important;\nflex-direction:row!important;\n}\n\n{{ sid }} .icon-grid.icon-grid{\ndisplay:flex;\nflex-direction:column;\nflex:1 0 calc((100%/3) - (var(--gap)*2)/3);\nwidth: calc((100%/3) - (var(--gap)*2)/3);\nalign-items:start;\nborder:1px solid #D9D9D9;\nborder-radius:16px;\npadding: clamp(8px,1.67vw,32px);\ngap:16px!important;\n}\n\n{{ sid }} .icon-grid *:not(li){\nmargin:0!important;\nletter-spacing:0;\n}\n\n{{ sid }} .icon-grid h4{\n width:100%;\n}\n\n{{ sid }} .icon-grid img{\nborder-radius:50%!important;\nwidth:clamp(60px,5.23vw,100px);\naspect-ratio:1/1;\n}\n\n{{ sid }} ol{\n margin:0;\n}\n\n{{ sid }} li{\n margin:5px;\n}\n\n{{ sid }} .img-text.right-image{\nflex-direction: row-reverse;\n}\n\n{{ sid }} .img-text.center,\n{{ sid }} highlight.icon-grid.icon-grid{\ntext-align:center;\nalign-items: center;\n}\n\n{{ sid }} .img-text div {\n  width: 58.5%;\n  gap:clamp(16px,1.25vw,24px);\n}\n\n@media(max-width:768px){\n{{ sid }} .icons-grid{\n justify-content:center;\n}\n\n{{ sid }} .icon-grid.icon-grid{\n flex:1 0 calc((100%/2) - (var(--gap)*2)/3);\nwidth: calc((100%/2) - (var(--gap)*2)/3);\n align-items:center!important;\n}\n\n\n{{ sid }} .img-text,\n{{ sid }} .img-text div{\nmax-width:100%!important;\ntext-align:center;\n}\n{{ sid }} .icon-grid *:not(li){\ntext-align:center!important;\n}\n\n\n{{sid}} .custom-html,\n{{sid}} .chapters,\n{{sid}} nav-heading{\npadding-left:0!important;\npadding-right:0!important;\n}\n}\n</style>"
